The problem in the provided Tundra code is that it should print "review", b
but it prints "pass". The condition score > threshold should have been fals
false. This means the score (72) is not greater than threshold (80), so the
the program has to execute the else branch and prints "pass" instead of "re
"review". 

Here's how we can fix the code:

```tundra
val score = 72;
val threshold = 80;

if(score > threshold) {
  print("review");
} else {
  print("pass");
}
```
This program should now correctly print "review" when run, as the condition
condition `score > threshold` is false. The score of 72 is not greater than
than the threshold of 80. Therefore, it will execute the if branch and prin
prints "review". If the condition was true (e.g., if score was 90), then it
it would print "pass" instead.
